he basic tool we use is convex programming duality. In the special case of\nconvex programs with linear constraints (but convex objectives), we show a\nparticularly simple way of obtaining dual programs, putting it almost at par\nwith linear program duality. This simple way of finding duals has been used\nsubsequently for many other applications.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 21 Sep 2016 18:02:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-09-22"}
