ombining the hydrogen and carbon results we arrive at a firm lower limit\nto the cosmic ray ionization rate of 2.5$\\times$10$^{-18}$ s$^{-1}$, but the\nactual value is likely much larger.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 22 Sep 2016 08:11:37 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 26 Oct 2016 12:50:04 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-12-14"}
