\nJ0, but not for J45.\n  Conclusions: FCLs measured in myopic eyes showed a similar performance than\nthe reported in previous ray-tracing studies with a small bias explained by the\nmanufacturing process and the lens decentration. Two-dimensional maps are\npreferable for assessing J45 changes due to the lens.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 21 Sep 2016 18:17:47 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 13 Oct 2016 16:09:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-10-14"}
